<h1 class="gl-mb-5 gl-text-size-h2">
NVIDIA - GitLab-Master
</h1>
<div id="js-custom-sign-in-description"><p data-sourcepos="1:1-1:120" dir="auto">This is the SCM Team supported Gitlab instance open to all in the company.   Use your NVIDIA SSO credentials to login.</p>&#x000A;<p data-sourcepos="3:1-3:177" dir="auto">There is no need to register for an account any longer; just login with SSO and your account will be created.  Service accounts are no longer allowed to register for an account.</p>&#x000A;<p data-sourcepos="5:1-5:45" dir="auto">Only the following credentials are supported:</p>&#x000A;<ul data-sourcepos="6:1-9:0" dir="auto">&#x000A;<li data-sourcepos="6:1-6:33">User Interface: NVIDIA SSO only</li>&#x000A;<li data-sourcepos="7:1-7:23">Git: Token or SSH Key</li>&#x000A;<li data-sourcepos="8:1-9:0">Docker (container registry): Token only</li>&#x000A;</ul>&#x000A;<p data-sourcepos="10:1-10:117" dir="auto">If you do not use the UI at least once every 3 months it will be automatically disabled.  To re-enable, simply login.</p>&#x000A;<hr data-sourcepos="12:1-12:3">&#x000A;<h1 data-sourcepos="13:1-13:24" dir="auto">&#x000A;<a id="user-content-export-control-warning" class="anchor" href="#export-control-warning" aria-hidden="true"></a>Export Control Warning</h1>&#x000A;<p data-sourcepos="15:1-15:194" dir="auto"><strong>There is no export control security built into GitLab as there is in Perforce; you <em>must not</em> store any export-controlled code, data or references in any controlled project on gitlab-master.</strong></p>&#x000A;<hr data-sourcepos="17:1-18:0">&#x000A;<p data-sourcepos="19:1-19:76" dir="auto">Find Help Here: <a href="https://confluence.nvidia.com/display/SCMU/GitLab-Master+FAQ" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">https://confluence.nvidia.com/display/SCMU/GitLab-Master+FAQ</a></p></div>
</div>
</div>
